From cou.: 39 The NMR spectra were recorded on Bruker AC 200 (1H at 200.13 MHz, 31P at 81.02 MHz and 195Pt at 50.32 MHz) and Bruker Avance DRX-300 (1H at 300.13 MHz, 31P at 121.49 MHz and 195Pt at 64.52 MHz) spectrometers with 5 mm Inverse probe, by using standard pulse sequences from the Bruker library. The chemical shifts (δ) are referenced to TMS (1H), external 85% H3PO4 (31P) and Na2PtCl6 (195Pt). The spectra of all nuclei (except 1H) were 1H decoupled. The 1H spectra were acquired in normal and 31P decoupled mode in the whole temperature range explored.
From Soup: 39 The NMR spectra were recorded on Bruker AC 200 ( 1 H at 200.13 MHz, 31 P at 81.02 MHz and 195 Pt at 50.32 MHz) and Bruker Avance DRX-300 ( 1 H at 300.13 MHz, 31 P at 121.49 MHz and 195 Pt at 64.52 MHz) spectrometers with 5 mm Inverse probe, by using standard pulse sequences from the Bruker library. The chemical shifts ( δ ) are referenced to TMS ( 1 H), external 85% H 3 PO 4 ( 31 P) and Na 2 PtCl 6 ( 195 Pt). The spectra of all nuclei (except 1 H) were 1 H decoupled. The 1 H spectra were acquired in normal and 31 P decoupled mode in the whole temperature range explored.
 ###### 
From cou.: 40 2D 31P-Chemical exchange spectra were acquired by the method of Bodenhausen et al.22 using 1024 data points in t2 for 128 t1 values and a pulse repetition delay of 1.5 s for mixing times ranging from 100 to 500 ms. 2D NMR data sets were zero-filled to 512 points in the t1 dimension and apodised with a shifted sinebell function.
From Soup: 40 2D 31 P-Chemical exchange spectra were acquired by the method of Bodenhausen et al . 22 using 1024 data points in t 2 for 128 t 1 values and a pulse repetition delay of 1.5 s for mixing times ranging from 100 to 500 ms. 2D NMR data sets were zero-filled to 512 points in the t 1 dimension and apodised with a shifted sinebell function.
