From cou.: 42 Complexes 1–3 were obtained and purified according to literature methods.5b The CD2Cl2 solutions for the NMR measurements were in the range 0.04–0.01 M.
From Soup: 42 Complexes 1–3 were obtained and purified according to literature methods. 5b The CD 2 Cl 2 solutions for the NMR measurements were in the range 0.04–0.01 M.
 ###### 
From cou.: 43 All manipulations were carried out at 195 K under a purified N2 atmosphere by using standard Schlenk techniques. 7.8 mg of dppe (19.6 μmol) was dissolved in 0.5 ml of CD2Cl2 and added to a violet solution of 3 (25 mg, 19.7 μmol in 0.5 ml CD2Cl2) into an NMR tube. The resulting mixture, which immediately turned yellow, was transferred into the spectrometer probe, pre-cooled at 195 K for 1H and 31P measurements. The NMR spectra were acquired each 30 min alternating 1H and 31P observation and raising the temperature, in 10 K steps, from 193 to 273 K. The sample was then stored at 253 K and measured again, after 7 days, in the 300–203 K range.
From Soup: 43 All manipulations were carried out at 195 K under a purified N 2 atmosphere by using standard Schlenk techniques. 7.8 mg of dppe (19.6 μmol) was dissolved in 0.5 ml of CD 2 Cl 2 and added to a violet solution of 3 (25 mg, 19.7 μmol in 0.5 ml CD 2 Cl 2 ) into an NMR tube. The resulting mixture, which immediately turned yellow, was transferred into the spectrometer probe, pre-cooled at 195 K for 1 H and 31 P measurements. The NMR spectra were acquired each 30 min alternating 1 H and 31 P observation and raising the temperature, in 10 K steps, from 193 to 273 K. The sample was then stored at 253 K and measured again, after 7 days, in the 300–203 K range.
 ###### 
From cou.: 44 The preparation of this sample was performed directly into a NMR tube at room temperature. 0.5 ml of solution of 1 (0.039 M in CD2Cl2) and of 3 (0.041 M in CD2Cl2) were mixed and the resulting solution was inserted into the spectrometer probe. The 1H and 31P NMR spectra were recorded at 300 K immediately after the preparation and after 2 h standing at the same temperature. The VT measurements were performed in the range 213–300 K. 2D 31P-Chemical exchange spectra were acquired at 273 and 300 K. The sample was stored at low temperature and reanalysed after 5 days at 300 K (in 1H observation, 500.13 MHz) and after 20 days (in 1H, 1H{31P} and 195Pt observations).
From Soup: 44 The preparation of this sample was performed directly into a NMR tube at room temperature. 0.5 ml of solution of 1 (0.039 M in CD 2 Cl 2 ) and of 3 (0.041 M in CD 2 Cl 2 ) were mixed and the resulting solution was inserted into the spectrometer probe. The 1 H and 31 P NMR spectra were recorded at 300 K immediately after the preparation and after 2 h standing at the same temperature. The VT measurements were performed in the range 213–300 K. 2D 31 P-Chemical exchange spectra were acquired at 273 and 300 K. The sample was stored at low temperature and reanalysed after 5 days at 300 K (in 1 H observation, 500.13 MHz) and after 20 days (in 1 H, 1 H{ 31 P} and 195 Pt observations).
